**Why src/ Layout**
- Prevents accidental imports from local source (tests run against installed package)
- Forces proper package installation in editable mode
- Catches import errors that would break in production

**Why One Assert Per Test**
- Test failures pinpoint exact issue (no "which assertion failed?")
- Each test has single, clear purpose
- Easier to skip/xfail individual behaviors

**Why Fixtures (not setUp/tearDown)**
- Composable: fixtures can use other fixtures
- Explicit: test signature shows dependencies
- Scoped: control when setup/teardown runs
- Modular: share fixtures via conftest.py

**Why TDD (Red-Green-Refactor)**
- Red: test defines behavior contract before implementation exists
- Green: minimal code to pass (prevents over-engineering)
- Refactor: safe cleanup with tests guarding correctness
